<p>GDP growth: 9.9% GDP: $124bn (PPP: $152bn) Inflation: 13.9% Population: 20.2m GDP per head: $6,160 (PPP: $7,560)</p>

<p>A 2010 constitutional reform removed the inconvenience of presidential elections, and although legislators face the voters this year victory for forces loyal to President Eduardo dos Santos is a foregone conclusion. Policy will focus on the transition to sustained growth after post-conflict rebuilding. Progress will be hampered by vested interests and the fiscal burden from fuel subsidies. Oil revenues will keep growth racing ahead.</p>

